<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Automated"><PMID Version="1">41448315</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2026</Year><Month>01</Month><Day>29</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>01</Month><Day>29</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print-Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1879-0003</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>339</Volume><Issue>Pt 1</Issue><PubDate><Year>2026</Year><Month>Jan</Month></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>International journal of biological macromolecules</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Int J Biol Macromol</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Enhancing the gel properties of pork Myofibrillar protein with silkworm Pupa protein-carrageenan pickering emulsion.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>149873</StartPage><MedlinePgn>149873</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1016/j.ijbiomac.2025.149873</ELocationID><ELocationID EIdType="pii" ValidYN="Y">S0141-8130(25)10430-3</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>To investigate the effects of silkworm pupa protein-carrageenan Pickering emulsion (SCPE) on gel properties of myofibrillar protein (MP), stable SCPE was prepared, and then the structure and physicochemical properties of SCPE and MP co-gel were evaluated. Compared with the control group, when the ratio of SCPE to MP ranged from 1:10 to 7:10, the strength, surface hydrophobicity, DPPH free radical scavenging ability and vitamin A embedding rate of the gel were significantly enhanced (p&#xa0;&lt;&#xa0;0.05). Dynamic rheological analysis proved the composite gel formed an elastic gel structure. Furthermore, the increased intermolecular forces, &#x3b2;-folding and &#x3b2;-turning content of gel after the addition of SCPE, indicated the enhanced stability of the gel. When the ratio of SCPE to MP was 7:10, the gel exhibited the best texture stability and VA embedding efficiency. Pearson correlation analysis showed SCPE synergistically improved composite gel texture, hydrophobic interaction, and VA embedding rate by regulating MP gel secondary structure and surface charge. This study lays a theoretical foundation for developing protein-based food colloids with good texture.</AbstractText><CopyrightInformation>Copyright &#xa9; 2025 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.</CopyrightInformation></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Yuanyuan</LastName><ForeName>Zeng</ForeName><Initials>Z</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Life Science, Anhui Normal University, Wuhu, Anhui, 241000, PR China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Yinghao</LastName><ForeName>Xu</ForeName><Initials>X</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Life Science, Anhui Normal University, Wuhu, Anhui, 241000, PR China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Cancan</LastName><ForeName>Luo</ForeName><Initials>L</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Life Science, Anhui Normal University, Wuhu, Anhui, 241000, PR China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Yingying</LastName><ForeName>Li</ForeName><Initials>L</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Life Science, Anhui Normal University, Wuhu, Anhui, 241000, PR China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Yanan</LastName><ForeName>Zang</ForeName><Initials>Z</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Life Science, Anhui Normal University, Wuhu, Anhui, 241000, PR China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Linjie</LastName><ForeName>Xu</ForeName><Initials>X</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Life Science, Anhui Normal University, Wuhu, Anhui, 241000, PR China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Ji</LastName><ForeName>Luo</ForeName><Initials>L</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>College of Life Science, An